The paper deals with the problem of computing maximal independent sets (MIS) and generalized maximal independent sets (GMIS) in hypergraphs in a distributed computing setting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Data Structures and Algorithms, Social and Information Networks, Networking and Internet Architecture, and Computational Complexity categories. Among these, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the problem of distributed computing and data structures/algorithms. cs.SI and cs.NI are also likely categories as they deal with social and information networks and networking and internet architecture, respectively, which are relevant to the problem of hypergraph computation. Finally, cs.CC is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and presents efficient algorithms.
